CV-screening systems are classified as **high-risk AI** under Annex III, Category 4(b) of the EU AI Act because they make employment recruitment decisions affecting candidates' fundamental rights and opportunities. The primary verifiable property is **non-discrimination compliance**: the system must demonstrate equal accuracy, false positive/negative rates, and selection outcomes across protected attributes (gender, ethnicity, age, disability) to satisfy the fairness and bias mitigation requirements. This requires continuous statistical parity monitoring, documentation of training data demographics, and impact assessments showing the model doesn't disproportionately exclude protected groups. Additional verifiable properties include human oversight mechanisms, explainability of rejection decisions, and compliance with record-keeping obligations under Articles 12 and 28 of the AI Act.
